                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17426a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to all
                            <gloss type="to">American Consular Officers in Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-10T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following statement has just been given to the press by the President: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>An adequate force will be sent at once in pursuit of Villa with the
                            single object of capturing him and putting a stop to his forays. This
                            can and will be done in entirely friendly aid of the constituted
                            authorities in Mexico and with scrupulous respect for the sovereignty of
                            that Republic.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
